# Auth and Collaboration Rules

## Authentication

- **Supabase Auth** (email/password): `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` (browser), `server.ts` (server components), `middleware.ts` + `src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts` (session refresh / protected routes).
- **Public:** `/saq` landing (CTA when logged out). **Protected by middleware:** `/saq/assessment/*`, `/saq/dashboard/*`, `/saq/report/*` → redirect to `/login?next=…`.
- **Email confirmation:** `signUp` uses `emailRedirectTo` → `/auth/callback?next=/saq`. Configure **Site URL**, **Redirect URLs** (include `/auth/callback`), and optional `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` in env (see `env.example`).

## Persistence (auth-related tables)

- **`profiles`** — one row per `auth.users` user (optional `full_name`, `organisation_name`).
- **`assessments.owner_user_id`** — required; creator is owner.
- **`assessment_collaborators`** — `assessment_id`, `user_id`, `role` (`owner` | `editor` | `reviewer` | `viewer`), `invited_by`; owner row mirrors ownership. RLS uses `SECURITY DEFINER` helpers (e.g. `rls_user_has_assessment_access`) to avoid policy recursion on collaborators.

## Permissions (single source of truth)

- **`src/lib/saq/permissions.ts`** — `canViewAssessment`, `canEditAssessment`, `canManageCollaborators`, `canExportReport`, `canAccessDashboard`, etc. Use these instead of scattering role string checks in UI.
- **Repository:** `assessment.repository.ts` enforces access via `getAssessmentAccess`, RLS, and save/load guards.

## UI

- **Collaborators:** `AssessmentCollaboratorsPanel` on assessment flow; listing uses RPC where needed for emails.
- **Read-only:** viewers/reviewers get non-editable steps; use permission helpers + props (`readOnly`), not duplicate engine logic.

## Boundaries

- Do not persist derived SAQ results in DB; auth/collaboration tables are identity and access only.
- Engine modules remain free of Supabase and auth imports.
